properties.name: all good cafe
properties.description: Posted by Laughingcat 2934 Main Street, dallas texasaustin style breakfast, lunch and dinner - live music thurs, fri and sat night

properties.name: big bend national park
properties.description: Posted by Laughingcat  it\'s said that big bend is the grand canyon of texas without the crowds. i believe it.

properties.name: cafe izmir
properties.description: Posted by Laughingcat 3711 Greenville Ave, dallas texas

properties.name: nandina
properties.description: Posted by Laughingcat 5631 Alta Avenue, dallas texasaffordable, tasty, fresh late night sushi and thai food. all the rolls are delicious; esp lighten roll, lizard roll and volcano roll. you will walk out with a full tummy and funds left in your wallet.

properties.name: old monk
properties.description: Posted by Laughingcat 2847 henderson ave, dallas texasauthentic english pub. all the great beers you could hope for plus full bar. pub-type menu; check out fish and chips, roast beef sandwich and ploughman\'s lunch, tasty-tasty! this is the place to go when it\'s hot as hell august time in dallas. it\'s like a nice, cool, dark cave with elvis costello, the jam and the pogues piped in for your listening pleasure.

properties.name: state fair of texas
properties.description: Posted by Laughingcat  from the end of september to end of october all the experimental fried foods you could ever dream of. i highly recommend fried donkey tail (no donkeys are ever harmed in the making of this tasty treat, but hot dogs watch out!!), bbq\'d frito pie and fried oreos. once year i ate 7 frito pies over the fair season. glorious!!

properties.name: ten thousand waves
properties.description: Posted by Laughingcat  3451 Hyde Park Road, santa fe new mexicothey say that going to ten thousand waves in santa fe is like going to a traditional japanese obsen. i believe it.

properties.name: teppo
properties.description: Posted by Laughingcat2014 greenville ave, dallasthis is the best sushi and yakatori in downtown dallas by far. the food is fresh, tasty and a bit authentically off the wall. if they are on a wait they will let you in moosh, their private club. so deluxe. if you\'re wondering why i tagged elvis, go in, see for yourself.

properties.name: the dream cafe
properties.description: Posted by Laughingcat 2800 routh st, dallas texaskinda austin, kinda dallas, kinda world. breakfast lunch and dinner, healthy and tasty. veggies try "one for john" burger. good enchiladas and breakfast tacos.

properties.name: the kozy kitchen
properties.description: Posted by Laughingcat 4433 Mckinney Ave, dallas texasfresh, healthy breakfast and lunch. all meat is grass fed and veggies are organic where possible. ths place is hard to find (signs aren\'t obvious), but once you find it, you won\'t forget. it\'s across from cretia\'s on mckinney ave. free wifi.

properties.name: winchester mystery house
properties.description: Posted by Laughingcat 525 S. Winchester Blvd., San Jose, CA, United Statesthey say the winchester mystery masion is a really weird house. i believe it.
